base walloper
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:an alteration of gen. military base-wallah (with pun on <i>base</i> `bum'), a soldier, esp. an officer, employed behind the lines at base; a member of Base Staff; base-walloper, -wallower, bludger, bum-buzzard.
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
